data.reddit:
*Apologies for the novel I’m about to write - there’s been a lot going on.*

5’1” (155cm), 120lb (54.5kg), white

Existing medical issues: Narcolepsy w/o cataplexy, generalized anxiety, depression (cyclothymia), multidirectional instability in R shoulder (from 2011, but causes stiff neck on one side occasionally), migraines

In the past 2 months, I’ve been diagnosed with gastritis and a flare-up of IBS due to daily nausea, abdominal cramping, and dizziness. I’ve also been experiencing persistent insomnia, decreased appetite, and weight loss due to extreme stress and anxiety since mid-June after an unsuccessful 3-week trial of Xyrem (GHB). For the unfamiliar, narcoleptics often do experience insomnia. I had my first appointment with a dietician this past Tuesday and have been seeing my therapist weekly.

Regular medications: Wellbutrin 450mg/daily, Lamictal 200mg/daily, Vyvanse 70mg/daily, Adderall 20mg/as needed but typically daily, Mirena (levonorgestrel IUD), Excedrin migraine as needed, Botox every 3 months for migraines

Recent medications I’m still taking: Ambien 5mg/nightly, Protonix 40mg/daily, Bentyl 10mg/as needed (haven’t today), Zofran-ODT 4mg/as needed (none since Wednesday)

In sum, I’m a mess and haven’t seen much improvement in a while. I am very aware of the negative feedback-loop stress can have on your heath, which is why I want to check if this week has just been more of that.

So with all that out of the way...

I’ve been having an increasingly stiff neck and aching back, with especially sore trapezius muscles, since Monday night. Tilting my head to either side is painful. Touching chin to chest stresses the back of my neck and results in a delayed, dull pain. Folding up my legs with knees to chest doesn’t hurt initially, but after I stretched out again my spine slowly started to have an increasing “burning” pain. I’ve primarily been on the loveseat sitting up with my legs stretched out and toes flexed (I’m juuuust long enough that I can’t point them on here), and when my cats try to nap in my lap that stresses my back.

I’ve also had a persistent headache this week, but not as bad as a migraine. Photosensitivity also isn’t as bad as I’ve had before, if unremarkable. I’ve noticed I am especially irritated by loud audio, though, which is unusual.

Despite this summer’s sleep pattern of falling asleep between 3:00-6:00am (hence the Ambien), I’ve been tired enough to fall asleep before midnight these past two nights. I slept 12hrs Thursday night and 14hrs last night - but that’s the standard for being narcoleptic, so maybe that’s just a sign of my sleep finally getting back on track.

I haven’t and still don’t have an abnormal temperature (reading 98.6F with oral thermometer), but today I’m feeling feverish. Eyes have that burning feeling behind them, face feels hot, clammy skin. House temp is 74F as per usual.

No vomiting.

**TL;DR** - My back and neck are stiff and achey accompanied by a headache. I’m feeling feverish but have no measurable fever. No photosensitivity, but audio sensitivity. I haven’t vomited. Energy is unreliable because I’m a narcoleptic. I’ve been increasingly stressed and anxious for the past several months.

A lumbar puncture is my nightmare medical test, so I’m not about to run to urgent care or the ER without serious reason. Thoughts?
